"to\": 423, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the longest race\", \"from\": 391, \"to\": 407}, {\"ngram\": \"a marathon\", \"from\": 412, \"to\": 422}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Benoit Samuelson ran it in the Olympics and won gold, proving to the world all that women were capable of.\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"score\": 0.9999269450483589, \"rank\": 7.306009703329532e-05, \"text\": \"Benoit\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\"}, {\"begin\": 431, \"end\": 440, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Samuelson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.380556347192789e-15, \"text\": \"Samuelson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q188094\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Samuelson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Samuelson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 463}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 489, \"to\": 498}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 508, \"to\": 513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The women's marathon had been left off the Olympic program for nearly a century because of rampant myths that running was dangerous for women.\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The women's marathon\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 552}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic program\", \"from\": 571, \"to\": 590}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly a century\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"rampant myths\", \"from\": 623, \"to\": 636}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As I wrote in my recent book,Better Faster Farther: How Running Changed Everything We Know About Women, track organizations around the world once banned women from running long distances, citing questionable sports-medicine studies, which claimed that women could not tolerate heat well, that extreme exertion would harm their reproductive organs, and that the activity would make them more masculine.\", \"from\": 675, \"to\": 1076, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my recent book\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 703}, {\"ngram\": \"Better Faster Farther\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 725}, {\"ngram\": \"Everything\", \"from\": 747, \"to\": 757}, {\"ngram\": \"Women\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 777}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 806, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 833}, {\"ngram\": \"long distances\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 861}, {\"ngram\": \"questionable sports-medicine studies\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 906}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 932}, {\"ngram\": \"extreme exertion\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 984}, {\"ngram\": \"their reproductive organs\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1021}, {\"ngram\": \"the activity\", \"from\": 1032, \"to\": 1044}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Others simply believed that women did not have the endurance-even though, by the time Benoit Samuelson was a teenager, many had already proved they did.\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1229, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1163, \"end\": 1169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"score\": 0.9999269450483589, \"rank\": 7.306009703329532e-05, \"text\": \"Benoit\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\"}, {\"begin\": 1170, \"end\": 1179, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Samuelson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.380556347192789e-15, \"text\": \"Samuelson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q188094\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Samuelson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Samuelson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Others\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1083}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"the endurance\", \"from\": 1124, \"to\": 1137}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 1154, \"to\": 1162}, {\"ngram\": \"a teenager\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1194}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read: Why I hate sports but love the Olympics Still, adding a women's marathon to the Olympics seemed nearly impossible.\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Read\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1235}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 1248, \"to\": 1254}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1264, \"to\": 1276}, {\"ngram\": \"a women's marathon\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1309}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1313, \"to\": 1325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Before Benoit Samuelson's race, men made up 78 percent of Olympians, and the Games' longest running event for women was 1,500 meters.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1360, \"end\": 1366, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"score\": 0.9999269450483589, \"rank\": 7.306009703329532e-05, \"text\": \"Benoit\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q13219587\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Benoit\"}, {\"begin\": 1367, \"end\": 1376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Samuelson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.380556347192789e-15, \"text\": \"Samuelson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q188094\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Samuelson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paul_Samuelson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1388}, {\"ngram\": \"78 percent\", \"from\": 1397, \"to\": 1407}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1420}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games' longest running event\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1458}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 1463, \"to\": 1468}, {\"ngram\": \"1,500 meters\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1485}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women were not yet allowed to compete in other distance events.\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1550, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1492}, {\"ngram\": \"other distance events\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1549}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But women runners advocated for the marathon anyway, in a years-long campaign in which they organized races and teamed up with sports-science researchers to change the public perception of women runners.\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"women runners\", \"from\": 1555, \"to\": 1568}, {\"ngram\": \"the marathon\", \"from\": 1583, \"to\": 1595}, {\"ngram\": \"a years-long campaign\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1628}, {\"ngram\": \"races\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1658}, {\"ngram\": \"sports-science researchers\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1704}, {\"ngram\": \"the public perception\", \"from\": 1715, \"to\": 1736}, {\"ngram\": \"women runners\", \"from\": 1740, \"to\": 1753}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kathrine Switzer, a runner and one of the campaign's organizers, guessed that if the advocates had followed protocol, they would have had to wait decades for the marathon.\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1926, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1755, \"end\": 1771, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kathrine_Switzer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kathrine Switzer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kathrine_Switzer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kathrine_Switzer\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a runner\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1781}, {\"ngram\": \"the campaign's organizers\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1818}, {\"ngram\": \"the advocates\", \"from\": 1836, \"to\": 1849}, {\"ngram\": \"protocol\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1871}, {\"ngram\": \"decades\", \"from\": 1901, \"to\": 1908}, {\"ngram\": \"the marathon\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, it was added in 1984.\", \"from\": 1927, \"to\": 1957, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The magnitude of that success set a powerful precedent.\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 2014, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The magnitude\", \"from\": 1959, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"that success\", \"from\": 1976, \"to\": 1988}, {\"ngram\": \"a powerful precedent\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2013}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the years that followed, the Olympics opened up not just to women marathoners but to female athletes in all sports.\", \"from\": 2015, \"to\": 2133, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2027}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2043, \"to\": 2055}, {\"ngram\": \"women marathoners\", \"from\": 2078, \"to\": 2095}, {\"ngram\": \"female athletes\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2118}, {\"ngram\": \"all sports\", \"from\": 2122, \"to\": 2132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When the modern Games began, women were not allowed to compete at all.\", \"from\": 2134, \"to\": 2204, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the modern Games\", \"from\": 2139, \"to\": 2155}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2168}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the next roughly nine decades, 50 women's events trickled in; men, meanwhile, earned nearly 100 new opportunities to show off their athleticism.\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2354, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the next roughly nine decades\", \"from\": 2210, \"to\": 2239}, {\"ngram\": \"50 women's events\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2258}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2275}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly 100 new opportunities\", \"from\": 2295, \"to\": 2323}, {\"ngram\": \"their athleticism\", \"from\": 2336, \"to\": 2353}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But since the marathon was added, the number of total Summer Olympic events for women has nearly tripled, to 151 today, and the number of men's events has stayed close to steady.\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2533, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the marathon\", \"from\": 2365, \"to\": 2377}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 2389, \"to\": 2399}, {\"ngram\": \"total Summer Olympic events\", \"from\": 2403, \"to\": 2430}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2440}, {\"ngram\": \"the number\", \"from\": 2479, \"to\": 2489}, {\"ngram\": \"men's events\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2505}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Soonall new sportshad to have female competitors.\", \"from\": 2534, \"to\": 2583, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"female competitors\", \"from\": 2564, \"to\": 2582}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, on the 40th anniversary of the women's marathon, the Olympics hasfinally achieved 50-50 gender parity.\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2691, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 40th anniversary\", \"from\": 2592, \"to\": 2612}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's marathon\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2636}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2650}, {\"ngram\": \"50-50 gender parity\", \"from\": 2671, \"to\": 2690}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Women had been running marathons for nearly a century before the Olympics allowed them in.\", \"from\": 2693, \"to\": 2783, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Women\", \"from\": 2693, \"to\": 2698}, {\"ngram\": \"marathons\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2725}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly a century\", \"from\": 2730, \"to\": 2746}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2754, \"to\": 2766}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At first they did so illicitly-including at the inaugural 1896 Olympic marathon, when one female racer completed the 26.2 mile course the day after the men.\", \"from\": 2784, \"to\": 2940, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the inaugural 1896 Olympic marathon\", \"from\": 2828, \"to\": 2863}, {\"ngram\":